page.title: 11Ryton Woods
page.content: Ryton Woods(168.54 acres)lies at the apex of the A445 and A423 roads,S.E.of Coventry.A Site of Scientific Interest it was purchased on Feb.6,1985 by WARNACT for Â£100000.The site is a pedunculate oak/hazel woodland with a regular breeding popn.of nightingales, 6 species of warbler,3 of woodpecker, breeding birds of prey and tree pipits.Several patches of small leaved lime trees indicate an ancient woodland,as does the presence of wood millet.Bluebells,honeysuckle and bramble are abundant and there are primroses,wood sorrel and yellow pimpernel.The rich tree popn.includes silver and downy birch,spindle,guelder rose,dogwood,holly,rowan and field maple.The sunlit glades are home to white admiral,wood white,purple hair- streak,comma,ringlet,brimstone and peacock.A small pool also exists.
